Description: Fixed % fee rate| e.g. 0.02563 would be 2.563%.     For display purpose| the percentage figure is rounded up to 2 decimal places. In the example| it will be 2.57%.     In the case of an investment management fee of a portfolio| it can have multiple fixed percentage fee profiles. (It cannot be in sliding scale). In the case of a portfolio management fee| it can have one fee profile only. Hence there is no need to add this element for the same portfolio and same master book kind. However| the value is still rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.

This element indicates whether the fee for a portfolio is reported in the section  Investment management fee  or  Portfolio management fee .  Btfg$book_kind (cached table)   USER_ID INTL_ID NAME INVST_MNGT btfg$invst_mngt Investment management fee TMP_MNGT btfg$tmp_mngt Portfolio management fee  From business perspective| the fee charged by ready-made portfolio and tailored made portfolio are reported in the section  Investment management fee  and  Portfolio management fee  respectively.  Hence| the UI needs to select the corresponding btfg_master_book_kind_id for reporting fees in the  Investment management fee  and  Portfolio management fee  sections.

The existence of tariff_factor path of a btfg$book_kind_id indicates that the fee is a fixed percentage fee for the btfg$book_kind_id.  For each book kind| the tariff_factor and tariff_bnd_list are mutually exclusive.

Fixed % fee rate| e.g. 0.02563 would be 2.563%.  For display purpose| the percentage figure is rounded up to 2 decimal places. In the example| it will be 2.57%.  In the case of an investment management fee of a portfolio| it can have multiple fixed percentage fee profiles. (It cannot be in sliding scale). Hence this element is added up for the same portfolio and same master book kind and then rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.  In the case of a portfolio management fee| it can have one fee profile only. Hence there is no need to add this element for the same portfolio and same master book kind. However| the value is still rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.

The existence of tariff_bnd_list path of a btfg$book_kind_id indicates that the fee is a sliding scale fee for the btfg$book_kind_id.  For each book kind| the tariff_factor and tariff_bnd_list are mutually exclusive.
The presence of this path indicates the existence of SMSF administration fee.
The presence of this path indicates the existence of SMSF bundled administration fee.
Receiving a value in tariff_amt in this path indicates dollar fee component exists.

As the business sets up discount for SMSF administration fee as a percentage| the spcd_offset_val_type_id will be 9. The details of the code is available in Btfg$cost_ovr_type (cached table)  ID INTL_ID USER_ID NAME 9 spcd_perc_disc SPCD_PERC_DISC Discount in %  Appendix A (Avaloq Fee Concept) provides an explanation of how the special condition codes work. It is intended for general knowledge only. The steps describe below has already taken into account how the business intends to use the system and is sufficient for the current UI build.  Use the following steps to calculate the SMSF administration fee net of discount. 1. For each btfg_book_kind_id (i.e. component) of the SMSF administration fee where spcd_offset_val_type_id is equal to 9| calculate net fee amount of the component = tariff_amt * (1   (spcd_offset_val / 100)) 2. The net fee amount of each component (i.e. each of the amount calculated in first step) of SMSF administration fee  is rounded up to 2 decimal places. 3. This element shows the underlying components (cost profile) of a fee. The underlying components of an investment management fee of a portfolio can have multiple components which are listed below. (Btfg$book_kind cached table)  USER_ID INTL_ID NAME INVST_MNGT_IM btfg$invst_mngt_im Investment management fee - Invst. mgr. INVST_MNGT_RE1 btfg$invst_mngt_re1 Investment management fee - Resp. entity 1 INVST_MNGT_RE2 btfg$invst_mngt_re2 Investment management fee - Resp. entity 2  The underlying components of a portfolio management fee of a portfolio can have one component only which is listed below. (Btfg$book_kind cached table) USER_ID INTL_ID NAME TMP_MNGT btfg$tmp_mngt Portfolio management fee

This element indicates whether the fee for a portfolio is reported in the section  Investment management fee  or  Portfolio management fee . Btfg$book_kind (cached table)  USER_ID INTL_ID NAME INVST_MNGT btfg$invst_mngt Investment management fee TMP_MNGT btfg$tmp_mngt Portfolio management fee  From business perspective| the fee charged by ready-made portfolio and tailored made portfolio are reported in the section  Investment management fee  and  Portfolio management fee  respectively. Hence| the UI needs to select the corresponding btfg_master_book_kind_id for reporting fees in the  Investment management fee  and  Portfolio management fee  sections.

Fixed % fee rate| e.g. 0.02563 would be 2.563%. For display purpose| the percentage figure is rounded up to 2 decimal places. In the example| it will be 2.57%. In the case of an investment management fee of a portfolio| it can have multiple fixed percentage fee profiles. (It cannot be in sliding scale). Hence this element is added up for the same portfolio and same master book kind and then rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI. In the case of a portfolio management fee| it can have one fee profile only. Hence there is no need to add this element for the same portfolio and same master book kind. However| the value is still rounded up to 2 decimal places before displaying on UI.

The existence of tariff_bnd_list path of a btfg$book_kind_id indicates that the fee is a sliding scale fee for the btfg$book_kind_id.  For each book kind| the tariff_factor and tariff_bnd_list are mutually exclusive.
